        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 11:51PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 1151 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Loma Alta, moving north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Us-277 Near The Sutton-Edwards County Line, Vinegarone, and Loma
Alta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
